<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06215018 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06215018 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  PAST; BASEBALL; PROFESSIONAL; DEATH; OBITUARY  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Chris Short, who pitched in the major leagues for 15 years, died Thursday in aWilmington, Del., convalescent home. He was 53.;    Short had a rupturedaneurysm 2 1/2 years ago and fell into a coma from which he never regainedconsciousness.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Sports  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  EX-PHILLIES PITCHER SHORT DIES AT 53  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Baseball Notes  </MEMO><TEXT>     Short pitched 14 years with the Philadelphia Phillies, winning 17 or moregames four times in a five-year period starting in 1964.;    He was named tothe All-Star team in 1964 and 1967.;    Short ended his career with theMilwaukee Brewers in 1973.;  ETC.: Milwaukee placed infielder Gary Sheffieldon the 15-day disabled list retroactive to July 26 because of a bad shoulderand activated pitcher Edwin Nunez. . . . Third baseman Gary Scott, theopening-day third baseman for the Chicago Cubs after hitting .400 in springtraining, probably will miss the rest of the season with a broken hand afterbeing hit by a pitch in a Triple-A game in Des Moines, Iowa. . . . New YorkYankees pitcher Pascual Perez will start Sunday for Double-A Albany as part ofhis rehabilitation from a shoulder injury. . . . The condition of Bostonreliever Jeff Gray, who collapsed in the clubhouse Tuesday, is &quot;about thesame,&quot; said team physician Arthur Pappas. He said doctors are optimistic thatGray had a spasm or a migraine attack and not a stroke when he became dizzy,his speech became slurred and he felt weakness in his right side. Graysuffered a similar attack while at Florida State 10 years ago. . . .Pittsburgh pitcher Rick Reed, who was called up Wednesday and gave up a homerun that keyed Atlanta's six-run fifth inning, was sent back to Triple-ABuffalo. . . . St. Louis reliever Todd Worrell is hopeful of pitching inSeptember after undergoing arthroscopic surgery to repair a partially tornrotator cuff in his right shoulder.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910802  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Friday  </DAY><MONTH>  August  </MONTH><PG.COL>  4D  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  321  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Friday August 2, 199100215018,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>